 to customers about collection, eg a poster in your shop</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Sending batteries to be recycled</h3>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s not essential, but you can ask a battery compliance scheme to collect your batteries free of charge - search online to join one or call the Environment Agency to get advice on joining a scheme.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Environment Agency Helpline</strong><br />\n03708  506 506<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 6pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>In Scotland, contact the Scottish Environment Protection Agency Helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Scottish Environment Protection Agency</strong><br />\n01786 457700</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>In Northern Ireland, contact the Northern Ireland Environment Agency Batteries Helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Northern Ireland Environment Agency Batteries Helpline</strong><br />\n028 9056 9382</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To transport batteries yourself, eg to a recycling plant, you need a licence and have to follow the law on  <a href=\"/dispose-hazardous-waste\" title=\"dispose of hazardous waste\">hazardous waste</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Vehicle Certification Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle Certification Agency\">VCA</abbr>) officers can visit your premises to make sure you are complying with the law.</p>\n\n<h3>Smaller retailers</h3>\n<p>Retailers selling fewer than 32 <abbr title=\"kilogram\">kg</abbr> don’t have to run a take-back scheme. If you decide to take waste batteries back you may have to arrange collection and transport for recycling yourself and follow the law on <a href=\"/dispose-hazardous-waste\" title=\"dispose of hazardous waste\">hazardous waste</a>. Speak to a compliance scheme operator first - they may offer a collection.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/battery-waste-producer-supplier-responsibilities/battery-producers","slug":"battery-producers","order":3,"title":"Battery producers","body":"<h2>Portable batteries</h2>\n\n<p>The regulations for collection, treatment and recycling depend on the amount of batteries you put on the market.</p>\n\n<h3>1 tonne or more per year</h3>\n<p>You must pay for the collection, treatment, recycling and disposal of waste batteries. You do this by joining a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/business/regulation/111038.aspx\" title=\"Battery Compliance Scheme\">Battery Compliance Scheme.</a></p>\n\n<p>They will:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>register you with the Environment Agency (<abbr title=\"Environment Agency\">EA</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>collect, treat and recycle waste batteries</li>\n  <li>send information to the <abbr title=\"Environment Agency\">EA</abbr> about the collection to recycling process</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Less than 1 tonne per year</h3>\n<p>You must register directly with the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/business/regulation/111042.aspx\" title=\"Environment Agency\">Environment Agency.</a></p>\n\n<p>You can join a Battery Compliance Scheme to dispose of your waste batteries.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re starting a new battery business you must register within 28 days of putting batteries on the market.</p>\n\n<h3>Producers of industrial and vehicle batteries</h3>\n<p>You must <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/business/regulation/111046.aspx\" title=\"register with the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills\">register with the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (<abbr title=\"Department for Business, Innovation and Skills\">BIS</abbr>).</a> </p>\n\n<p>You have to take back any waste batteries your customers bring you, whether they bought them from you or not. Producers of vehicle batteries don&rsquo;t have to take batteries from consumers, just from garages, scrap yards, end of life vehicle treatment sites and civic amenity sites.</p>\n\n<p>You must tell customers how they can return waste batteries, eg on your website.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/battery-waste-prod