aste.aspx\" title=\"special waste\">Scottish Environment Protection Agency</a> can help you check if your waste is hazardous.</p>\n\n<h3>Northern Ireland</h3>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.doeni.gov.uk/niea/waste-home/regulation/regulations_hw/further_information.htm\" title=\"waste regulations\">Northern Ireland Environment Agency</a> can help you check if your waste is hazardous.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/dispose-hazardous-waste/duty-of-care","slug":"duty-of-care","order":2,"title":"Duty of care","body":"<h2>Your responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>You must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>consider alternatives to disposal - eg, recycling </li>\n  <li><a href=\"/dispose-hazardous-waste/storage\" title=\"Storing waste\">store your waste</a> safely and securely </li>\n  <li>fill in a <a href=\"/dispose-hazardous-waste/consignment-notes\" title=\"Consignment notes\">consignment note </a> for each load of hazardous waste you transport </li>\n  <li>fill in a <a href=\"/dispose-hazardous-waste/consignee-returns\" title=\"Consignee returns\">consignee return</a> if you receive a delivery of hazardous waste</li>\n  <li>check that any business you use to deal with your hazardous waste is licensed, and keep proof of this - eg, take a copy of their licence </li>\n  <li>usually have a licence to transport, store, treat, recover or dispose of hazardous waste yourself  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Find a licensed waste business</h3>\n\n<h4>England, Wales and Northern Ireland</h4>\n\n<p>There are public registers you can use to find:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/netregs/links/98247.aspx\" title=\"Find a licensed waste business\">business that can recycle or dispose of your waste</a></li>\n  <li>a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/netregs/links/98247.aspx\" title=\"Find a collection company to take away your waste\">collection company to take away your waste</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Scotland</h4